{"lemma":"تَمْر","slug":"تَمْر","root":"ت.م.ر","root_slug":"ت-م-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-م-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4108","n4109","n4112"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"date (fruit)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"تَمْر\nAs a widely cultivated plant, the native distribution of the date-palm even in earlier antiquity is questionable. Particular terms relating to date culture, like شِيص (šīṣ, “unfecundated dates”), قَسْب (qasb, “dried dates”), and كَافُور (kāfūr, “bract of the inflorescence of the date palm”) can be borrowed. Assuming that ثَمَر (ṯamar, “fruits”), and Old South Arabian 𐩻𐩣𐩧 (ṯmr /⁠ṯamar⁠/, “fruits”), is the same word generalized from an original meaning “dates”, the present word تَمْر (tamr) and Old South Arabian 𐩩𐩣𐩧 (tmr /⁠tamr⁠/, “dates”) are declared, together with Hebrew תָּמָר (tāmār), reborrowed from Aramaic תמרא / ܬܡܪܐ (tamrē, “dates”), in which language only Proto-Semitic *ṯ /θ/ becomes t /t/, and the vowel a is reduced to ə and then ∅ in such position."},"ipa":["/tamr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4108","headword_ar":"تَمَرَ","root":"tmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tm~r","text_ar":"تمّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatomiyrN","text_ar":"تَتْمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Atmr","text_ar":"اتمر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed"},{"kind":"text","text":"people"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave"},{"kind":"text","text":"them"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to eat,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamor","text_ar":"تَمْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n4109","headword_ar":"تمّر","root":"tmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatomiyrN","text_ar":"تَتْمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dried"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) dates. (S.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dried"},{"kind":"text","text":"flesh-meat: (T, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he cut"},{"kind":"text","text":"flesh-meat"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into small pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, * IAth, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and dried it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, IAth, K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna laA yaraY biAlt~atomiyri baA^osFA","text_ar":"كَانَ لَا يَرَى بِالتَّتْمِيرِ بَاْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He used not to see any harm in cutting flesh-meat into small pieces, like dates, and drying it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, in a Mohrim's thus preparing flesh-meat for travelling-provision; or in one's drying the flesh of wild animals before the state of ihrám. (IAth.) ―         -b3-  See also 1: ―         -b4-  and 4, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","T","IAth"]},{"entry_id":"n4112","headword_ar":"تَمْرٌ","root":"tmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a coll. gen. n.; (S, A;) masc. in one dial. and fem. in another [like other nouns of the same class]; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the palmtree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabiybN","text_ar":"زَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to grapes, by general consent of the lexicologists: (Mgh, Msb:) the dates are left upon the palmtree, after they have become ripe, until they are dry, or nearly so, when they are cut, and left in the sun to dry thoroughly; and sometimes, as AHát says, the fruit of the palm-tree is cut when full-grown but unripe, to lighten the tree, or from fear of theft, and left until it becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamor","text_ar":"تَمْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tumuwrN","text_ar":"تُمُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tumoraAnN","text_ar":"تُمْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Msb, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"varieties"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamor","text_ar":"تَمْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; for a coll. gen. n. has not a pl. in the proper sense: (S:) and in like manner the dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamoraAni","text_ar":"تَمْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sorts"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamor","text_ar":"تَمْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Sb cited in the M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bsr","text_ar":"بسر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorapN","text_ar":"تَمْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamaraAtN","text_ar":"تَمَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busorN","text_ar":"بُسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTi","text_ar":"اَعْطِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axaAka tamorapF faA_ino A^abaY fajamorapF","text_ar":"اَخَاكَ تَمْرَةً فَاـِنْ اَبَى فَجَمْرَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give thou thy brother a dried date; and if he refuse"},{"kind":"text","text":"it,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a live coal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~amoru biAls~awiyqi","text_ar":"التَّمْرُ بِالسَّوِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dried dates with meal of parched barley"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is another prov., used in allusion to requital. (Lh.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajada Einodahu tamorapa AlguraAbi","text_ar":"وَجَدَ عِنْدَهُ تَمْرَةَ الغُرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He found with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at his abode, what he approved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosuhu tamorapN bika*aA","text_ar":"نَفْسُهُ تَمْرَةٌ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His mind is pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agreeably affected, with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by, such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consents to such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K. * [Accord. to the TA, it is here like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariHapN","text_ar":"فَرِحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this seems to be true as to the meaning; not as to the form of the word. See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vmr","text_ar":"ثمر"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vamirN","text_ar":"ثَمِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEoniY","text_ar":"دَعْنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a nafosiY gayoru tamorapK","text_ar":"اـِنَّ نَفْسِى غَيْرُ تَمْرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let me alone: verily my mind is not pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN hinodiY~N","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ هِنْدِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the tamarindtree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus called in the present day;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumarN","text_ar":"حُمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawomarN","text_ar":"حَوْمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmr","text_ar":"حمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["M","Mgh","Msb","T","S","K"]}]}}